Dear Colleagues=2C

we are pleased to inform you that the second Workshop on Categorical Alg=
ebra=3A

CATALG2011 - =93Recent developments and future perspectives=94=2C

will take place in Gargnano (GARDA lake) from September 27th to October =
1st 2011=2E

Our idea is to organise a true =22workshop=22=2C with only a few invited=
  talks=2C some
open problem sessions=2C and some time for informal discussions=2E

The Scientific Committee (M=2E Gran=2C S=2E Mantovani and E=2EM=2E Vital=
e) decided to invite
Dominique Bourn=2C George Janelidze and Marco Grandis as Main Speakers=3A=
  they will give an invited 2 hour talk and chair a 1 hour =22open proble=
m session=22=2C jointly with a member of the Scientific Committee=2E

Besides the three Main Speakers=2C the Scientific Committee invited for =
a 1 hour talk=2C
a few leading researchers in categorical algebra=2C namely T=2E Everaert=
=2C T=2E Janelidze=2C Z=2E Janelidze=2C
S=2E Lack=2C G=2E Metere=2C D=2E Rodelo and T=2E Van der Linden=2E All o=
f them have confirmed their presence=2E

Finally=2C Walter Tholen kindly accepted to close the workshop with the =
last talk=2E

Although there will be no other scheduled talk=2C there will be an open =
poster session to present
and discuss results and investigations in categorical algebra=2E

The workshop will start with a welcome buffet on Tuesday September 27th=2C=
  in the late afternoon=2E
Talks are scheduled from Wednesday September 28th=2C in the morning=2C t=
ill Saturday October 1st=2C
before noon=2E

The website of the conference can be found at the address

http=3A//users=2Emat=2Eunimi=2Eit/users/metere/Gargnano2011/

In order to register you should complete the Registration Form here belo=
w=2C
and e-mail it to catalg2011=40unimi=2Eit before August 31st=2E

We are looking forward to seeing you in Gargnano!

Best regards=2C


Sandra Mantovani and Giuseppe Metere
on behalf of the Organizing Committee

